main event: Multiple sightings of disc-shaped objects in Spokane, Washington, between September 3 and 8, 1951.
interesting points: Three to five disc-shaped objects observed at approximately 3500-4000 feet., Objects observed with the naked eye and binoculars., The objects were blue and white and exhibited erratic maneuvers., Speed of objects varied between 30 to 50 mph., No sound was reported during the sightings.
witness description: AF Officers including Captains and Majors, and their spouses
